# Tunnel Rules

## Why a tunnel exists (not Windows-only)

Cursor Override Base URL traffic is sent from **CursorÔÇÖs cloud**, which
SSRF-blocks private/loopback addresses. A local gateway therefore needs a
**public HTTPS** front door. This is architectural, not a Windows quirk.

**Never** ÔÇťsimplifyÔÇŁ by pointing Cursor at `127.0.0.1`.

Tunnel is **provider-agnostic**: one public Base URL fronts the gateway; Moonshot
vs DeepSeek routing happens inside the gateway after alias resolve (`gateway.mdc`).

